* ==========================================================================
* clusters.asm — GENERATED by tools/gen-clusters.py, do not hand-edit.
* --------------------------------------------------------------------------
* 8 cluster patterns of 4 members (master + 3 satellites).
*
* Every dx is a multiple of 4. That is not cosmetic: it is the reason a
* satellite's VRAM address is master_addr + a CONSTANT delta, sharing the
* master's plane and nibble. See the header of tools/gen-clusters.py.
*
* |dx| <= 28 and |dy| <= 28, which is what lets starfield.asm skip the
* per-member clip test when the master is at 28 <= x <= 131, and clamp a
* master's spawn y to [28, 171] so a cluster never leaves the screen
* vertically at all.
*
* Per member: fdb delta (dy*40 + dx/4), fdb dx sign-extended, fdb dy*40.
* dx and dy*40 are for the clip test: the render adds them to the master's x and
* cached row to decide whether this member is on screen at all.
* The master is member 0 at delta 0, so the render loop needs no special case.
* ==========================================================================

CL_PATS    equ 8
CL_MEMBERS equ 4
CL_DX_MAX  equ 28
CL_DY_MAX  equ 28
CL_MEMSIZE equ 6                 ; fdb delta + fdb dx16 + fdb dyrow
CL_PATSIZE equ 24                ; bytes per pattern

